Several students from South Eastern Kenya University in Kitui were on Sunday injured after their bus lost control and rolled several times at Kwa Gonza, Kitui County. Kenya Red Cross said in a tweet that the injured were rushed to the Mwingi Sub-county hospital with the assistance of the police,EMS and well-wishers. The bus which was taking the students to Kwa Gonza market for shopping lost control and rolled near the Kenyatta University campus gate. Students at the university rushed at the scene and helped with the evacuation exercise. Click here for the latest political news  